    {
      "id": "7bebcac5f0557052a900f2d466731698cd219b7b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-25 16:37:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(11 inline comments)\n\nTests look generally good, though some cleanups are needed. \n\nOne thing that came to mind while inspecting this is that resize of a filesystem with data in it to a smaller one may result in inodes being moved during the rename in order to be able to free the itable blocks in the last group(s) being removed. This may result in an inconsistency in the OI mapping for these inodes.\n\nA question for Fan Yong is whether OI FID-to-inode lookups verify the found inode with the LMA FID each time, and trigger an OI scrub if not?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
