        "subject": "LU-3485 tests: Add resize2fs testing for OST/MDT filesystems",
        "message": "LU-3485 tests: Add resize2fs testing for OST/MDT filesystems\n\nAdd testing of the MST and OST filesystems with resize2fs.\nCurrently, only offline resizing is possible until LU-137\nis finished. Thus, each file system is unmounted and\ne2fsck is run before and after the resize to check for\nerrors.\n\nWe are restricting the number of OSTs since large-lun\ntest 2 run time is based on the number of OSTs and can\ntime out if there are 16 OSTs as in the last large-lun\ntest results. We've also increased the verbose flags\nto llverfs to track where all the time is being spent.\n\nTest-Parameters: testlist=large-lun ostcount=4 \\\nmdsfilesystemtype=ldiskfs mdtfilesystemtype=ldiskfs \\\nostfilesystemtype=ldiskfs\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I7207ce4c4e6771fc128c8b1d02d15d453b8556ae\n"
      },
